## Limitations

The findings are based on available literature and studies, which may not cover all aspects of the relationship between social media and sleep. The data primarily focuses on adolescents and young adults, potentially overlooking the effects on other age groups. Additionally, the causality between social media use and sleep disturbances remains complex and not fully understood, as many studies highlight correlation rather than causation. Further research is needed to explore these dynamics comprehensively.